1
00:00:12,370 --> 00:00:14,471
{\an1}So how the hell am I
supposed to beat that guy?

2
00:00:15,138 --> 00:00:17,672
{\an1}Well, that I don't know,
I'm afraid.

3
00:00:18,238 --> 00:00:23,041
{\an1}Uh, hey, hold on, Octopops
trained here too, didn't he?
I can just go and ask him!

4
00:00:25,341 --> 00:00:29,144
{\an1}No. he's never going to tell
me. Not with his attitude.

5
00:00:29,811 --> 00:00:30,712
Perhaps...

6
00:00:32,312 --> 00:00:34,947
{\an7}<i>I wonder if Octopops</i>
<i>had a dark side too?</i>

7
00:00:37,648 --> 00:00:38,781
Hey, Motoi?

8
00:00:40,449 --> 00:00:43,717
Can you help me out?
Can you tell me more
about Octopops?

9
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:47,218
Like, how he grew up,
and what his
personality is like.

10
00:00:47,485 --> 00:00:49,820
{\an1}Maybe I can get a few
hints from all that stuff.

11
00:00:51,253 --> 00:00:55,289
{\an1}Then I can figure out what's
different between us and why he
can control his Tailed Best!

12
00:00:57,489 --> 00:01:02,025
{\an1}If you're also a Jinchuriki,
you know what it's like to
live with that burden.

13
00:01:02,058 --> 00:01:03,726
{\an1}Tell me, isn't that true?

14
00:01:04,126 --> 00:01:05,760
{\an1}Yeah, I do know
all about it.

15
00:01:05,993 --> 00:01:09,762
{\an1}And he should be able
to understand what it's
been like for me, too!

16
00:01:11,796 --> 00:01:15,198
{\an1}To be honest, I don't
normally like to prattle
on about other people.

17
00:01:16,732 --> 00:01:21,034
But Naruto, you're
also a Jinchuriki just
like Master Bee is.

18
00:01:22,667 --> 00:01:25,502
{\an1}And controlling the Nine Tails
will lead to world peace.

19
00:01:26,902 --> 00:01:27,703
{\an1}I'll do it.

20
00:01:27,737 --> 00:01:29,104
Ah! Thank you!

21
00:01:30,738 --> 00:01:32,139
{\an1}<i>Now, I told you earlier,</i>

22
00:01:33,305 --> 00:01:37,774
{\an1}<i>As a fellow Jinchuriki,</i>
<i>you know what it's like</i>
<i>to live with that burden.</i>

23
00:01:41,008 --> 00:01:42,676
{\an1}As you can well imagine.

24
00:01:43,777 --> 00:01:47,678
Incredible power breeds
dread and ill feelings.

25
00:01:49,946 --> 00:01:53,914
{\an1}<i>Master Bee was long feared and</i>
<i>resented by the other villagers.</i>

26
00:01:54,447 --> 00:01:59,382
{\an1}<i>But he never got depressed or</i>
<i>complained, not even once.</i>

27
00:01:59,416 --> 00:02:03,618
{\an1}<i>He was always cheerful,</i>
<i>continuously working</i>
<i>the people around him.</i>

28
00:02:04,385 --> 00:02:09,421
{\an1}<i>Instead of feeling shame</i>
<i>at being a Jinchuriki,</i>
<i>he turned it into a positive.</i>

29
00:02:10,421 --> 00:02:15,791
{\an1}<i>It seemed to me that he decided</i>
<i>to take pride in himself and</i>
<i>even added self-expression.</i>

30
00:02:15,824 --> 00:02:16,290
Yo!

31
00:02:17,724 --> 00:02:21,193
{\an1}And the main reason that
he was able to take pride
in being a Jinchuriki,

32
00:02:22,392 --> 00:02:23,594
{\an1}<i>Was probably,</i>

33
00:02:24,094 --> 00:02:27,062
{\an1}<i>thanks to his older brother,</i>
<i>the Raikage.</i>

34
00:02:29,262 --> 00:02:31,497
{\an1}For ages now,
to prevent betrayal,

35
00:02:32,165 --> 00:02:39,135
{\an4}Jinchuriki have almost always
been selected from blood
relations of the Five Kage,
like siblings or spouses.

36
00:02:40,235 --> 00:02:44,170
{\an1}A Jinchuriki is both an ultimate
power to protect the Kage,

37
00:02:44,569 --> 00:02:47,238
{\an1}And a symbol of the
Kage's ultimate strength.

38
00:02:48,571 --> 00:02:54,207
{\an1}<i>I believe Master Bee strove</i>
<i>diligently to become a worthy</i>
<i>Jinchuriki for Lord Raikage.</i>

39
00:02:55,908 --> 00:03:00,276
{\an1}<i>It is said that he mastered</i>
<i>this Waterfall of Truth</i>
<i>challenge in no time at all.</i>

40
00:03:02,245 --> 00:03:03,544
{\an1}I have deep respect,

41
00:03:03,778 --> 00:03:06,379
{\an1}for the kind of
person Master Bee is.

42
00:03:07,247 --> 00:03:10,313
{\an1}In my eyes,
he is a true hero.

43
00:03:11,082 --> 00:03:13,182
{\an1}To be such a
well-loved Jinchuriki,

44
00:03:14,183 --> 00:03:18,152
{\an1}Master Bee must be
quite a great man.
And you must be, too.

45
00:03:18,751 --> 00:03:19,551
{\an1}Ah...

46
00:03:20,952 --> 00:03:22,987
Wait, that's it!
I've got it!

47
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:26,687
You can go ask Ocotopops
for training hints on my
behalf, Motoi!

48
00:03:26,721 --> 00:03:28,022
Would you please
do that for me?

49
00:03:28,388 --> 00:03:30,489
{\an1}I'm sorry.
I can't.

50
00:03:30,523 --> 00:03:32,290
Aaagh!
Come on!
Why not?!

51
00:03:33,557 --> 00:03:35,858
{\an1}I am not worthy of
such an errand.

52
00:03:36,926 --> 00:03:37,692
Huh?

53
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:42,494
{\an1}Because... I once tried
to kill Master Bee!

54
00:03:42,861 --> 00:03:43,762
[gasp]

55
00:05:25,806 --> 00:05:30,842
"Killer Bee and Motoi"

56
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:35,410
But why?! You said
that you respected
Octopops! Just now!

57
00:05:39,645 --> 00:05:41,479
I'm sure there's
some explanation.

58
00:05:44,514 --> 00:05:46,115
{\an1}So, what was it, tell us?!

59
00:05:47,616 --> 00:05:49,382
{\an1}It's time I confessed.

60
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:55,320
{\an1}Since you're a Jinchuriki
too, I think it's okay to
tell you about that incident.

61
00:05:56,820 --> 00:05:58,154
{\an1}Incident?
What do you mean?

62
00:05:59,454 --> 00:06:02,189
{\an1}It all took place
30 years ago.

63
00:06:06,691 --> 00:06:09,092
[roar]

64
00:06:17,629 --> 00:06:21,297
{\an1}<i>Back then, the Jinchuriki</i>
<i>that contained the Eight Tails,</i>

65
00:06:21,331 --> 00:06:24,765
{\an1}<i>wasn't strong enough</i>
<i>to completely control</i>
<i>the Tailed Beast.</i>

66
00:06:25,632 --> 00:06:30,701
{\an1}<i>The Eight Tails would get</i>
<i>loose, rampage, and wreak</i>
<i>havoc on the Hidden Cloud.</i>

67
00:06:31,135 --> 00:06:37,503
{\an4}Each time, the previous
Raikage-Lord Third-would
stop the Eight Tails
with his elite force.

68
00:06:38,138 --> 00:06:41,139
Listen! I need you
to hold the Eight
Tails still!

69
00:06:41,772 --> 00:06:44,908
{\an1}And while you're doing that,
I'll imprison him in the
Sealing Urn.

70
00:06:45,374 --> 00:06:46,175
{\an1}Understood.

71
00:06:46,608 --> 00:06:48,142
Okay! Get to it.

72
00:06:53,677 --> 00:06:53,978
{\an1}(om throwing effort)

73
00:06:54,812 --> 00:06:56,179
[roar]

74
00:07:02,848 --> 00:07:03,582
[snort]

75
00:07:08,718 --> 00:07:10,118
Huaaagh!

76
00:07:11,552 --> 00:07:12,887
[roar]

77
00:07:14,888 --> 00:07:15,454
Aaah!

78
00:07:18,089 --> 00:07:20,357
Damn it! The
Sealing Jutsu chain!

79
00:07:20,990 --> 00:07:24,225
{\an1}We can't give up!
Or the Hidden Cloud Village
will be destroyed!

80
00:07:32,028 --> 00:07:32,861
There. Got him.

81
00:07:45,567 --> 00:07:49,936
[big roar]

82
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:52,403
Now move in!
Pin him down!

83
00:07:58,840 --> 00:08:01,474
{\an1}Back off, accursed humans!

84
00:08:11,845 --> 00:08:13,013
Yaaahh!

85
00:08:16,915 --> 00:08:18,648
[roar]

86
00:08:20,216 --> 00:08:20,782
Huaah!

87
00:08:24,550 --> 00:08:31,687
[roaring]

88
00:08:36,089 --> 00:08:41,058
[panting]

89
00:08:42,393 --> 00:08:47,694
{\an4}<i>Every time, they somehow</i>
<i>managed to subdue the</i>
<i>Eight Tails and shove him</i>
<i>back into the Sealing Urn.</i>

90
00:08:48,527 --> 00:08:50,461
{\an1}<i>There were always</i>
<i>casualties.</i>

91
00:08:52,729 --> 00:08:58,132
{\an4}<i>However, despite the risk, it</i>
<i>was crucial to possess the Eight</i>
<i>Tails to preserve the balance of</i>
<i>power between the nations.</i>

92
00:08:59,866 --> 00:09:02,600
{\an1}So the Jinchuriki
experiments continued.

93
00:09:06,669 --> 00:09:07,603
{\an1}(cm mild sitting effort)

94
00:09:09,137 --> 00:09:11,537
{\an1}And among the many
countless casualties...

95
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:19,409
[distraught]

96
00:09:21,676 --> 00:09:22,976
{\an1}<i>...was my father.</i>

97
00:09:27,878 --> 00:09:29,845
{\an1}You lost your father
to Master Bee.

98
00:09:30,713 --> 00:09:31,513
So that's why--

99
00:09:31,746 --> 00:09:32,579
{\an1}That's not it.

100
00:09:37,115 --> 00:09:39,684
{\an1}Master Bee and I were
close friends once.

101
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:45,219
{\an1}We were both only five years
old when my father fell.

102
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:50,188
{\an1}Ha ha ha!
Yea-eah!

103
00:09:54,190 --> 00:09:55,090
{\an1}You did it, Bee!

104
00:09:55,123 --> 00:09:55,891
Ha ha ha!

105
00:09:56,091 --> 00:09:56,857
Ha ha!

106
00:10:00,025 --> 00:10:00,960
Ah?!

107
00:10:10,164 --> 00:10:16,299
{\an4}<i>The Jinchuriki responsible</i>
<i>for my father's death,</i>
<i>died when the Eight Tails</i>
<i>was extracted and sealed.</i>

108
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:18,633
{\an1}<i>That was the</i>
<i>previous Jinchuriki.</i>

109
00:10:48,981 --> 00:10:53,782
{\an1}<i>It was after that tragedy that</i>
<i>Master Bee was chosen to be the</i>
<i>Eight Tails' Jinchuriki.</i>

110
00:10:55,183 --> 00:10:57,750
{\an1}Why, then?
Why try to
kill Master Bee?

111
00:11:00,319 --> 00:11:03,387
{\an1}I assumed that it
wasn't possible to
control the Eight Tails.

112
00:11:04,486 --> 00:11:08,255
{\an1}<i>I believed that there</i>
<i>would always continue</i>
<i>to be more victims.</i>

113
00:11:24,628 --> 00:11:27,931
{\an1}<i>My hatred toward the</i>
<i>Eight Tails continued to grow.</i>

114
00:11:29,198 --> 00:11:30,432
{\an1}<i>I was only a child...</i>

115
00:11:30,466 --> 00:11:32,933
{\an1}<i>But all I could think</i>
<i>about was getting revenge.</i>

116
00:12:00,911 --> 00:12:05,247
{\an4}Got a song in my heart
that's gotta come out,
it's gonna make y'all
scream and shout,

117
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:09,216
{\an1}ain't no doubt the rhymes I
spout are what I'm all about.
Yeah!

118
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:13,884
{\an1}Ain't nothing gonna keep me down
or make me frown, yo!

119
00:12:13,917 --> 00:12:16,952
{\an1}<i>Master Bee...</i>
<i>was always laughing.</i>

120
00:12:21,254 --> 00:12:26,189
{\an1}<i>I started hating him more</i>
<i>and more because it seemed</i>
<i>like he didn't care at all.</i>

121
00:12:27,490 --> 00:12:32,226
{\an1}My hatred of Eight Tails shifted
to Master Bee, his Jinchuriki.

122
00:12:34,292 --> 00:12:35,227
I thought...

123
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:39,229
{\an1}if I killed Master Bee,
the Eight Tails would also die.

124
00:13:00,570 --> 00:13:01,371
Hm?

125
00:13:02,571 --> 00:13:03,139
[gasp]

126
00:13:04,639 --> 00:13:05,407
Ha ha!

127
00:13:16,944 --> 00:13:20,079
{\an1}So, I attacked Master Bee
from behind.

128
00:13:21,180 --> 00:13:25,282
{\an1}But when I failed, I became
terrified and ran away.

129
00:13:26,548 --> 00:13:31,850
{\an1}I had masked my face,
but it was possible that
Master Bee recognized me.

130
00:13:32,718 --> 00:13:35,752
{\an1}As a result,
I just stopped
talking to him.

131
00:13:37,820 --> 00:13:41,922
{\an1}But after all that,
how did you come to
respect Master Bee, then?

132
00:13:43,256 --> 00:13:45,656
{\an1}My hatred didn't
disappear overnight.

133
00:13:46,525 --> 00:13:50,826
{\an1}<i>For a long time, I continued</i>
<i>to follow Master Bee and</i>
<i>keep an eye on him.</i>

134
00:13:52,126 --> 00:13:54,361
{\an1}But, I wasn't the only one.

135
00:13:57,363 --> 00:14:01,164
{\an1}<i>Master Bee was shunned</i>
<i>and despised by the</i>
<i>villagers all the time.</i>

136
00:14:01,531 --> 00:14:04,832
Yo!
[beatboxes]
Yeah!

137
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:07,599
Huh??

138
00:14:19,338 --> 00:14:21,306
<i>Get lost!</i>
<i>You disgust me!</i>

139
00:14:22,339 --> 00:14:25,774
{\an1}<i>Even though he was forced</i>
<i>to become a Jinchuriki</i>
<i>because of politics,</i>

140
00:14:25,808 --> 00:14:28,575
{\an1}<i>and existed to</i>
<i>protect the village,</i>

141
00:14:28,608 --> 00:14:31,777
{\an1}<i>he continued to be</i>
<i>ostracized by the villagers.</i>

142
00:14:33,511 --> 00:14:33,977
[chuckle]

143
00:14:35,412 --> 00:14:38,713
{\an1}Oh, yeah? You think you're bad?
That's far from the worst
I've ever had.

144
00:14:38,747 --> 00:14:42,881
{\an1}Yo, yo, check it, yo!
I ain't gonna get mad,
I'll just keep being glad.

145
00:14:42,915 --> 00:14:44,316
{\an1}C'mon, c'mon, yo!

146
00:14:44,349 --> 00:14:45,950
Yo! Hey, yo!

147
00:14:52,986 --> 00:14:57,122
{\an1}<i>Almost anyone else would have</i>
<i>gone insane. And I realized,</i>

148
00:14:57,822 --> 00:15:00,789
{\an1}<i>Master Bee's suffering was</i>
<i>even greater than mine.</i>

149
00:15:02,491 --> 00:15:03,623
Why tell us this?

150
00:15:04,891 --> 00:15:07,460
Well, truth be told,
I'd rather have
Master Bee hear it.

151
00:15:09,427 --> 00:15:12,894
{\an1}But the reason that I'm
telling Naruto this,

152
00:15:12,928 --> 00:15:15,062
is that he's a
fellow Jinchuriki.

153
00:15:15,296 --> 00:15:15,963
Hm.

154
00:15:17,430 --> 00:15:20,865
{\an1}And yes, I am well aware
that I ought to tell Master Bee
the truth someday.

155
00:15:22,099 --> 00:15:24,700
{\an1}Or this isn't a true confession.

156
00:15:27,302 --> 00:15:30,403
{\an7}<i>[Dark Naruto]</i>
<i>Heh heh! </i>
<i>How convenient for him.</i>

157
00:15:30,769 --> 00:15:31,470
[gasp]

158
00:15:33,237 --> 00:15:33,804
{\an1}Heh heh!

159
00:15:34,871 --> 00:15:35,604
{\an3}Mm.

160
00:15:37,672 --> 00:15:39,307
{\an1}Naruto, where are you going?

161
00:15:40,974 --> 00:15:43,608
I just want to be
alone for a while.

162
00:16:02,616 --> 00:16:03,917
{\an1}It's that boy!

163
00:16:04,284 --> 00:16:06,085
I told you to stay
away from him!

164
00:16:06,285 --> 00:16:07,352
{\an1}Go away!!

165
00:16:10,453 --> 00:16:11,920
[cheering]

166
00:16:12,454 --> 00:16:13,921
{\an1}You're a hero, Naruto!

167
00:16:14,455 --> 00:16:16,590
Ha ha ha!
Thank you, Naruto!

168
00:16:18,290 --> 00:16:24,726
{\an4}To all of the people in
my village, I was a relic
of the past that they
wished would disappear.

169
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:31,129
{\an4}<i>[Temari]</i>
<i>Gaara's the Kazekage, remember?</i>
<i>Ugh! Show a little respect, </i>
<i>you nitwits!</i>

170
00:16:32,597 --> 00:16:37,631
{\an4}<i>[Matsuri]</i>
<i>Lord Gaara is the hottest</i>
<i>thing ever! He's a quiet, cool,</i>
<i>strong and elite warrior!</i>

171
00:16:38,932 --> 00:16:42,901
{\an7}<i>A lot of people</i>
<i>trust Octopops now.</i>
<i>He earned that from them.</i>

172
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:48,936
{\an7}<i>And Gaara's become Kazekage.</i>
<i>His village trusts him to</i>
<i>take care of them.</i>

173
00:16:49,470 --> 00:16:51,304
{\an8}<i>They accept and</i>
<i>respect him.</i>

174
00:16:52,606 --> 00:16:56,073
{\an7}<i>And me, I have Iruka Sensei,</i>
<i>and my comrades...</i>

175
00:16:56,773 --> 00:16:59,575
{\an4}Why didn't you give them
your autograph at Ichiraku?

176
00:17:00,575 --> 00:17:06,211
{\an1}Can't blame you, you know.
I mean, after all, they came
kissing up to you like that.

177
00:17:08,678 --> 00:17:11,380
{\an1}They were completely
disgusting, weren't they?

178
00:17:12,814 --> 00:17:13,747
Who the hell are you?

179
00:17:14,515 --> 00:17:16,149
{\an1}Don't you remember?

180
00:17:16,182 --> 00:17:20,551
{\an1}Everyone in the village used
to treat us like outcasts,
and then they try to pull that?

181
00:17:21,650 --> 00:17:27,387
{\an1}I am the real you. The one that
exists in your heart, I am you.

182
00:17:28,921 --> 00:17:32,222
{\an8}<i>The real me.</i>
<i>I never gave it</i>
<i>much thought.</i>

183
00:17:33,956 --> 00:17:36,291
{\an7}<i>But I guess somewhere</i>
<i>deep inside my heart,</i>

184
00:17:38,892 --> 00:17:44,528
{\an7}<i>It's true. I'm still not</i>
<i>confident that I have everyone's</i>
<i>trust back home in the village.</i>

185
00:17:55,166 --> 00:17:56,600
Where'd Naruto
run off to?

186
00:17:58,167 --> 00:17:59,368
Wait, you don't
think that...

187
00:17:59,568 --> 00:18:02,701
{\an1}This is a secret location.
An enemy couldn't possibly--

188
00:18:02,735 --> 00:18:03,603
<i>[Motoi]</i>
<i>Yaaagh!</i>

189
00:18:03,637 --> 00:18:06,304
{\an1}Huh? That sounded
just like old man Motoi!

190
00:18:13,207 --> 00:18:14,974
Augh! Rrgh!

191
00:18:15,841 --> 00:18:17,142
Huh? No! Motoi!

192
00:18:20,410 --> 00:18:22,511
{\an1}Naruto! Use Formation C!

193
00:18:23,578 --> 00:18:25,445
{\an1}Why?! Why's he doing this?

194
00:18:26,012 --> 00:18:27,346
{\an1}Naruto! Come on! Focus!

195
00:18:27,879 --> 00:18:30,314
{\an1}Stop, Octopops!
Just stop it!

196
00:18:31,215 --> 00:18:36,217
{\an1}Listen to me, okay?
Motoi really does trust you!
And he cares about you!

197
00:18:40,252 --> 00:18:43,253
That's the squid!
It isn't an
octopus at all!

198
00:18:44,053 --> 00:18:46,254
{\an1}What? A squid? Are you sure?

199
00:18:46,288 --> 00:18:47,855
{\an1}1, 2, 3, 4, 5...

200
00:18:47,888 --> 00:18:51,990
{\an1}You don't have to count!
